     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
==================================================== -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Modern estates, strong motorway access and consistent family demand.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Calamvale sits in Brisbane's outer southern corridor alongside Algester, Parkinson and Runcorn, approximately 18 kilometres south of the CBD. It is a suburb built primarily on residential estate development from the 1990s and 2000s, with modern brick homes on practical flat blocks that the family buyer segment consistently values for their low maintenance and clean presentation. Logan Motorway and Gateway Motorway access gives the suburb strong connectivity to both the CBD and the employment corridors to the south.
    </p>
