    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work the southern corridor regularly and understand Calamvale's buyer profile in depth. The most active buyers here are families making a considered purchase: they have a school-age brief, they need motorway access for work, and they are comparing Calamvale directly against Algester and Parkinson at a similar budget. Running a campaign in Calamvale means understanding those comparisons and positioning your specific property clearly against them.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The estate pockets in Calamvale carry a visual consistency that buyers in this segment find reassuring: well-maintained homes, park reserves built into the estate layout, walking paths, and a consistent streetscape. These features attract a buyer who values the predictability of an estate community and is prepared to pay for it relative to the older established alternatives in nearby Runcorn or Sunnybank. The suburb's proximity to the Logan Motorway at several access points makes the commute to the CBD viable, and the Gateway Motorway connection opens up both the airport corridor and the Redlands for work-related travel. Calamvale Community College and the nearby primary school catchments are actively researched by families making their suburb selection, and properties within catchment boundaries consistently attract stronger buyer competition at open homes.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229;">
