        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Calamvale's value is driven by its position in Brisbane's outer southern corridor, strong family buyer demand, and access to the Logan Motorway and Gateway Motorway interchange. The suburb's mix of modern residential estates and established homes on practical flat blocks appeals to families who want space and low-maintenance living at a price point below the inner-southern suburbs. School catchment access and estate presentation quality are the two most consistent differentiators between properties.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Calamvale?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented Calamvale homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days when accurately priced. The suburb draws a consistent family buyer pool from the southern corridor, particularly from buyers comparing Calamvale directly against Algester, Parkinson and Runcorn at similar price points. Modern estate homes with good presentation and school catchment access tend to attract inquiry quickly.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Calamvale?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Calamvale offers a practical outer-southern family lifestyle with good motorway access, local parks, and proximity to Sunnybank Hills shopping. The suburb has a strong community feel through its residential estates, and its flat topography makes it popular with families seeking easy outdoor living. The absence of heavy traffic through the suburb itself gives it a quieter residential character than its major road access might suggest.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Calamvale a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Calamvale offers consistent value for families seeking space and motorway connectivity in Brisbane's outer southern corridor. Its modern estate stock is well-maintained and the suburb sits at a price point where buyers get genuinely more land and home than comparable spend in Sunnybank Hills or Robertson. Family demand is reliable throughout the year and tends to intensify ahead of school enrolment windows.</p>
